%ncollide fixture - N-numbers in the byte range that used to collide with the
%<!...> ornament codes. Before the remap, N18/N19/N20/N21/N23 were dispatched
%as ornament marks (or nothing); N22 never collided. Post-remap all six render
%as their two-digit fret numbers. The final baroque chord combines an ornament
%(<!2mordent>) with a collision-range N-number (N20) to prove they no longer
%share a byte and render together correctly.
%
%The pinned upstream reference binary shares the collision defect, so its PS
%golden for these pages renders the ornaments instead of numbers; those pages
%are carved out of the PS byte-compare via PS_KNOWN_DIVERGENT (see run.ts and
%evals/REFERENCE.md "Known PS divergences"). The local-generated JSON golden
%pins the corrected output and is the real guard for these pages.

b
1-a N18
2-a N19
3-a N20
4-a N21
5-a N22
6-a N23
b

-b

b
1-a N20 c <!2mordent>
b
e
